I use a custom JavaScript template, that loses this when the new hash URL is generated. So I used it like so...<p><pre><code>    $(&#x27;a&#x27;).bind(&quot;mousemove&quot;, function(event){
            document.title = document.title.replace(&quot;▶&quot;,&quot;&quot;)
            $(&quot;audio&quot;).each(function(index) {
                if(!this.paused) {
                    document.title = &quot;▶ &quot; + document.title.replace(&quot;▶ &quot;,&quot;&quot;)
                    return false;
                }
            })
    });</code></pre>
